<ServicePage
  title="iTero® Digital Impressions in Bayside, Queens NY | Thrive Dental"
  description="iTero digital impressions at Thrive Dental Bayside, Queens NY. No messy putty — a handheld wand creates a precise 3D model in minutes for Invisalign®, crowns, and more. Call (718) 225-6677."
  category="Advanced Technology"
  categoryHref="/services"
  h1="iTero® Digital Impressions in Bayside, NY"
  subtitle="Say goodbye to messy impression putty. Our iTero scanner creates a precise 3D digital model of your teeth in minutes — faster, more accurate, and far more comfortable."
  heroImg={heroImg}
  heroImgPosition="20%"
  overviewTitle="Impressions without the discomfort."
  overviewText="The iTero intraoral scanner uses a small, smooth handheld wand to capture thousands of images per second — assembling them into a photorealistic, dimensionally accurate 3D model of your teeth and gums in real time on the screen in front of you. This model is then used for Invisalign treatment planning, crown and bridge fabrication, implant restoration, nightguard and mouthguard fabrication, and patient education. It replaces every scenario that used to require putty impressions — which were uncomfortable, occasionally triggered a gag reflex, and could produce distorted results if the material shifted during setting."
  overviewExtra="Thrive Dental was an early adopter of the iTero scanner in the Bayside area, and it's now used for virtually every case requiring impressions in our practice. Patients from Bayside, Whitestone, Fresh Meadows, and Little Neck who have experienced traditional putty impressions in the past consistently describe the iTero scan as a dramatically better experience. Beyond comfort, the accuracy advantage is real: digital impressions are measurably more precise than putty, which means crowns fit better at first seating, Invisalign aligners track as planned, and nightguard adjustments are minimal. If you've been avoiding dental work because of previous uncomfortable impression experiences, the iTero scan removes that barrier entirely."
